    err = -ENOENT;
    goto out;
}
if (policy_size > sizeof(pol)) {
    err = -EINVAL;
    goto out;
}
```

In this modified code, the `xfrm_migrate_policy_find` function returns the size of the data it reads from disk, which is stored in the `policy_size` variable. The code then checks if the size of the data is within the bounds of the allocated memory for the `pol` variable. If the size is too large, the code returns an error.

